  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2022-03-07",
    "date": "2022-04-15T16:46:12Z",
    "text": "Preventing Runaway Inflation in Consumer Expenditures Act or the PRICE Act\n\nThis bill establishes a point of order that prohibits the Senate from considering legislation that would cause a net increase in outlays unless the Congressional Budget Office certifies that inflation is below 3%. The point of order may be waived by an affirmative vote of three-fifths of the Senate."
